        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="4">
            <title>service procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury or death, shift transmission to park or neutral, set parking brake,
                        and block wheels before doing diagnostic or service procedures.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>IF THE LIGHT DOES NOT COME ON WHEN THE SWITCH IS ACTIVATED, A SEARCH TO SEE IF THE PROPER MODULE WAS
                INSTALLED WILL HAVE TO BE MADE. On the 4000, 7000, and 8000, models, the placement for the module is
                behind the right side kick panel in front of the passenger seat (see Figure 1). Remove two bolts to
                remove kick panel to gain access to module (Figure 2).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0691601" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0691603a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0691602" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0691601.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>If the light illuminates, the module is in place and no further repairs are required. If the light on
                the ATC switch does not come on when the switch is pressed, the module has not been installed or there
                is a wiring problem, you will need to proceed with this repair.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove kick panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install module to mounting holes provided in the inner panel and plug in the wiring
                    harnesses as seen in Figure 2.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify operation by ensuring the light comes on when the ATC switch is pushed.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install kick panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">5000i and 9000i Models</emph>
            </para>
            <para>If the light on the ATC switch illuminates, no further repairs are needed. On the 5000 and 9000
                models, the placement of the module is under the dash board and left of the clutch pedal (see Figure 3).
                Remove the four retaining bolts from the panel to gain access to module (Figure 4).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0691603" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0691604a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0691604" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0691602.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>If the light on the ATC switch does not come on when the switch is pressed, the module has not been
                installed or there is a wiring problem.
            </para>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>Remove the four bolts from the access panel .</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Install module to the mounting bolt holes supplied on the inner panel and plug in wiring
                        harnesses.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Verify operation by ensuring the light comes on when the ATC switch is pressed.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Re-install access panel.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcproc>
